9 An Act relating to education funding; creating the
Education Opportunities Enhancement Revolving Fund;
10 stating purposes of fund; providing for source of
funds; stating purpose of expenditures; prescribing
11 method of expenditures; providing for codification;
providing an effective date; and declaring an
12 emergency.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 35001 of Title 70, unless there
18 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
20 for the Oklahoma Department of Commerce to be designated the
21 "Education Opportunities Enhancement Revolving Fund". The fund
22 shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations,
23 and shall consist of all monies received by the Oklahoma Department
24 of Commerce from such sources as may be provided by law. All monies
Req. No. 16388 Page 1

1 accr uing to the credit of said fund are hereby appropriated and may
2 be budgeted and expended by the Oklahoma Department of Commerce as
3 may be necessary to enter into contract with a nonprofit entity
4 whose purpose is exclusively charitable and educational,
5 specifically to partner with school districts and agencies to
6 sponsor programs, workshops, and initiatives to eliminate barriers
7 to equitable opportunities and economic mobility for all students in
8 the Tulsa Metropolitan area. Expenditures from said fund shall be
9 made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer against claims
10 filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the Office of
11 Management and Enterprise Services for approval and payment.
12 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
13 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
14 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
15 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
16 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
